	Document(content="Note: Hi class! For those who are working with a partner on a Mini Project, it is your free will to decide how to collaborate. For instance, team members can collaborate offline, by sharing and updating the python scripts. Or, members can decide to use a shared GitHub repository to collaborate. However , given the settings of the GitHub assignment and the students' GitHub accounts administered by GitHub Classroom, it is not possible to add collaborators to the repository that you clone for the mini project from the Piazza link. Therefore, in order to collaborate within GitHub, it is suggested that 1) only one of the team members create a GitHub repository by accepting a link posted on the Piazza. 2) Team members create a separate 'local' GitHub repository, that is not tied to the GitHub Classroom, and collaborate using that. 3) After finishing the project, push all required files to the repository that we grade (the one cloned from the Piazza link). In this case, only one of the team members is responsible for pushing. Just make sure to clearly state the name of the collaborator on the report. In the same manner, only one of the team members can submit the report to the Gradescope. ", meta={'folders': ['project'], 'title': 'Instructions and Clarifications on GitHub Collaboration for Mini Project.', 'timestamp': '2022-11-21T19:23:33Z', 'user': 'l70jr826ufr9d', 'tags': ['instructor-note', 'project'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 259}),
