	Document(content="Note: Regarding Problem 1 - Condition#8 'Caution When a number is repeated in the input, increment hist[i] only once. For example, if there are three instances of 4 in data that comply with bin i, just increment hist[i] by 1, not 3.' The above condition might raise confusion in understanding the concept of histogram. The definition of histogram is to show how frequently a value falls into a particular bin. Following the definition of histogram, it is originally correct to increment the histogram bin by counting all number of values that comply with a particular bin, regardless of whether they are duplicated or not. In that sense, the Condition 8 of Problem 1 goes against the definition of histogram. Therefore, the Condition 8 of Problem 1 should rather only be interpreted as a preprocessing step for filtering the data points, prior to building a histogram. ", meta={'folders': ['hw2'], 'title': 'FAQ for Homework 2', 'timestamp': '2022-09-05T17:58:15Z', 'user': 'l70jr826ufr9d', 'tags': ['hw2', 'instructor-note', 'pin'], 'likes': 1, 'views': 285}),
