	Document(content="Question: How do we determine if an algorithm converged? I have seen the slides talking about algorithm convergence but didn't fully understand it Answer: When you recalculate the centers of the clusters, and if that is the same as the previous iteration, then the points are no longer moving (that is, all the points are in the clusters closest to them) and so the algorithm has converged. ", meta={'folders': ['exam'], 'title': 'Exam 3 Spring2022 Q2C', 'timestamp': '2022-12-12T02:24:56Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['exam', 'student'], 'likes': 3, 'views': 114}),
