	Document(content="Note: Hi! There have been a couple students who when they completed their denoising had the results be the exact same as the noise data. Basically, the denoising did not change their training data at all (values remained exactly the same). If this is also happening to you, try running your code in google colab. There may be some issue with the version of sklearn on your machine (I am not certain of this). This fixed their issue. You should see a different values for the accuracy of the models after the training data has been denoised. ", meta={'folders': ['project'], 'title': 'Project Path 3 Denoising Issue Fix', 'timestamp': '2022-12-07T18:27:04Z', 'user': 'kskmxecspaq4i1', 'tags': ['instructor-note', 'project'], 'likes': 2, 'views': 107}),
