	Document(content="Question: Hi! How were the values 17 and 10 calculated?? Answer: For pred_a, the Predictor object, self.coeffs = [4, 3] and x = [2, 3]. The predict method will calculate 4 * 2 + 3 *3 = 17. For pred_b, the Clip Predictor object, the same applies, but since clip was initialized to 10 and it is less than 17, 10 is returned. ", meta={'folders': ['exam'], 'title': 'Fall 2021 Exam 3 Question 3C', 'timestamp': '2022-12-06T17:51:32Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['exam', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 110}),
