	Document(content="Question: Part 3 says 'Can you use this data to predict what day (Monday to Sunday) is today based on the number of bicyclists on the bridges?' Do we have a whole set of data available to answer this? Are the program or the results supposed to come from only one single number? To be more specific, is the program supposed to predict a day based on a random number(say 9000) or? Answer: I believe that your goal would be to predict the day of the week based on the number of bicyclists on each bridge on that day. ", meta={'folders': ['project'], 'title': 'Project Path 1 Part 3', 'timestamp': '2022-12-05T22:11:02Z', 'user': 'ke6hswn31sc3ll', 'tags': ['project', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 126}),
	Document(content="Note: Hi all! Homework 10 grades have been released for all sections now. Everyone should be able to view their grades on Brightspace and their grading feedback in their Homework 10 repository on GitHub. To view your feedback, go to your Homework 10 repository on GitHub, click the drop-down menu under ‘master/main’ --> click ‘Tags’ --> click ‘graded.’ There will be a file called “grading_output.txt” in your repository which contains the autograder’s feedback along with how many points were earned for each question part. IMPORTANT NOTE ABOUT REGRADES: Due to the grading crunch of finals week and the project, I will only accept regrade requests made by 11:59pm on December 10th . If you believe an error has been made in grading, please send a regrade request immediately to ece20875.purdue.university@gmail.com . Remember to include the following information in your email: When submitting an email for a regrade request please do the following: Have a separate email for each HW regrade request Have the subject line be the following: HW# regrade request, in this case, HW10 regrade request . This makes it a lot easier for us to filter the inbox and find your email. Also, this a reminder to include the following information in your email: Relevant identifying information. For homework assignments, a link to your GitHub repository is needed. Section Number Grading item (e.g., homework 10) Purdue email (if not sent from a Purdue email) Your reasoning or explanation for a regrade, with specific details and justifications. ", meta={'folders': ['hw10'], 'title': 'Homework 10 Grades Released! (IMPORTANT NOTE ABOUT REGRADES)', 'timestamp': '2022-12-05T19:31:17Z', 'user': 'ktit8n4gsw8346', 'tags': ['hw10', 'instructor-note'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 196}),
