	Document(content="Question: I'm having trouble understanding the type of question that part 3 is wanting me to use. For example, classification or modeling. If anyone could explain this to me that would be great. I've tried graphing the data by day of the week to see if there was a pattern and there was not an evident pattern. Answer: The question essentially means - if you are given a number for the total number of bicyclists, can you, using the information that you are given, somehow come up with a way to tell what day it is? There is no particular 'way' that we are looking for. As you mentioned, you can think of classification and modelling as a few of the ways you can go about answering this problem. Remember you can also try multiple approaches (and not just restrict yourself to one, since this is an open-ended problem) and document them in your code and write-up. Finally, if you come to the conclusion/you find that you are not able to predict the day based on the total number of cyclists, you can explain your reasoning and the methods you used to supplement your argument. ", meta={'folders': ['project'], 'title': 'Final Project Path One Part 3', 'timestamp': '2022-12-05T03:48:19Z', 'user': 'ktnb8chh43f2xw', 'tags': ['project', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 122}),
