	Document(content="Question: I am a little confuse on why we should keep track of the value which moveToCluster returns, can someone please help me Answer: The value that move to cluster returns may be useful for deciding whether your clustering process has reached a final position, or one where updating your points and clusters no longer changes anything. ", meta={'folders': ['hw9'], 'title': 'HW9 P3', 'timestamp': '2022-11-21T00:50:18Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw9', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 70}),
	Document(content="Question: Can someone help me on the updatecenter function? I am confused by the wording in the helper section Answer: You should find the average value across all the dimensions for the points in self.points. For example, self.center.dim might equal 3, so each point in self.points would have an x, y, and z coordinate. You would find the average x coordinate, average y coordinate, and average z coordinate using the points in self.points, and make the new coordinates for self.center be equal to these average coordinates. ", meta={'folders': ['hw9'], 'title': 'Hw9 P2', 'timestamp': '2022-11-20T23:37:58Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw9', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 69}),
