	Document(content="Question: When determining how to solve for Problem 3, I ran into an issue where the points would end up in the opposite clusters. However, if I just copy/pasted the code used to move the points to the end of the updateCenter operation (essentially running through the points twice), and then updating the centers again it would produce the right value. I embedded some pseudocode to better detail it. Question: Why would this work? Answer: this is prob just a coincidence with this specific set where it settles after two loops (since we are just using a small dataset). what should happen is that you should just keep looping until stuff stops moving. ", meta={'folders': ['hw9'], 'title': 'HW9 Problem 3 Procedural Question', 'timestamp': '2022-11-16T20:52:32Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw9', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 131}),
