	Document(content="Question: Hello I am stuck on question 3 and am confused by the directions in the given function it says ' Move every point to its closest cluster (use Point.closest and # Point.moveToCluster)' the reason I am confused is are we supposed to import those functions from the class made in point.py and if so how do we do that? Answer: The 'closest' and 'moveToCluster' are object methods. Since you have already created point and cluster objects from the makePointList and createCluster, you can use these methods like you would use any other method. They do not need to be imported separately. ", meta={'folders': ['hw9'], 'title': 'Question 3', 'timestamp': '2022-11-15T01:42:20Z', 'user': 'ktnb65dyj24658', 'tags': ['hw9', 'student'], 'likes': 1, 'views': 141}),
	Document(content="Question: Is it not supposed to be that if p < alpha than we reject our Null Hypothesis. I am just confused what our Null Hypothesis is here ?. Isn't it supposed to be that the feature is significant ? Answer: The null is that the feature is not significant. Since you have a low pval, that means that given the null (that the feature is not significant) you have a very low probability of finding the results that you did. Because of this, you reject and decide that x1 is significant. I believe there’s an example in the notes as well where they set up the null as the feature being insignificant.", meta={'folders': ['exam'], 'title': 'Exam 2 Q6 part C', 'timestamp': '2022-11-14T10:40:19Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['exam', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 124}),
