	Document(content="Question: Im confused on how we are testing our model. Right now my code for part 8 goes from normalizing X directly to creating y^hat using the normalized X. With this, it is using the model that I created for the Apple data. When I plot it, the predicted shows a blue line at 0. This makes sense as the Apple data is very small compared to the google data. So are we supposed to create a new model based on the google data? Answer: No, you are not creating a new model for the Google data - you are testing the model that was trained on the Apple data. You wouldn't have a flat line for the predicted data; might want to check how you are normalizing the Google data and if your preprocessing of the CSV file is right (that is, if you have the right variables in the right place). ", meta={'folders': ['hw7'], 'title': 'Problem 2 Part 8', 'timestamp': '2022-10-28T12:58:19Z', 'user': 'ktnb63ymkyx5xg', 'tags': ['hw7', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 122}),
