	Document(content="Question: # Part 4# Function that trains a ridge regression model on the input dataset with lambda=l.# Input: Feature matrix X, target variable vector y, regularization parameter l.# Output: model, a numpy object containing the trained model. Is the the trained model the same as the predicted y values? Answer: The trained model is a `Ridge` object (see https://scikit-learn.org/stable/modules/generated/sklearn.linear_model.Ridge.html) that has had the `.fit` method called. ", meta={'folders': ['hw7'], 'title': 'HW 7 Problem 2 Part 4', 'timestamp': '2022-10-25T19:47:24Z', 'user': 'ktnb8chh43f2xw', 'tags': ['hw7', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 122}),
	Document(content="Question: Was just curious why we use a t test here? Shouldn't we only use t tests if we don't the sample population is below 30 and we don't know the standard deviation? The standard deviation is given in this question, so why would we still use the t value for this answer? Thanks Answer: There is a crucial difference between the population's standard deviation and the standard deviation of the sample. The standard deviation of the sample doesn't give us enough information to use a z-test. However, if we know the standard deviation of the population that the sample is taken from, then we can use a z-test. ", meta={'folders': ['exam'], 'title': 'Question about t test on Fall 2021 Exam 2', 'timestamp': '2022-10-24T23:32:46Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['exam', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 86}),
	Document(content="Question: I'm a little stumped on what this problem is asking and how to approach it. It seems very similar to part 1 if not identical, so what's the difference between part 1 and part 2, and is there a sample output that I could see to better understand what this part of the program is supposed to do? Thanks in advance! Answer: `normalize_test` is the same as `normalize_train` except you need to normalize using the training means and standard deviations rather than the testing means and standard deviations. ", meta={'folders': ['hw7'], 'title': 'Homework 7 Problem 2 Part 2', 'timestamp': '2022-10-24T21:10:23Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw7', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 116}),
