	Document(content="Question: Is the formula for B the same as it is for Linear Regression? As in, is applicable to a polynomial model as well? Answer: Yes ", meta={'folders': ['hw7'], 'title': 'HW7 Least Squares function', 'timestamp': '2022-10-22T21:37:53Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw7', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 124}),
	Document(content="Question: I'm confused what paramFits is supposed to look like. Do we call feature_matrix and least_squared and append the both outputs to paramFits? And where do we get the input parameters for feature_matrix and least_squared? Answer: It would probably be easier to fill in feature_matrix and least_squares first. feature_matrix takes in data, x, and a degree, d, and returns a feature matrix (see slides for how to construct the feature matrix). least_squares just implements the least squares equation (solution to beta) from the slides. For this part, you just have to implement the solution for beta given in the slides. This will return a list (or numpy array) of the coefficients of the model. In the main function, loop through each element in degrees. For each degree, you should call feature_matrix to construct your feature matrix. Then, call least_squares using the returned feature matrix from the previous step as input. The list that is returned by least_squares should be appended to paramFits. So, paramFits will be a list of lists OR could also be a list of 1D numpy arrays. ", meta={'folders': ['hw7'], 'title': 'Confused about HW7 Problem 1 main function', 'timestamp': '2022-10-22T01:11:17Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw7', 'student'], 'likes': 1, 'views': 129}),
