	Document(content="Question: Hi! I'm a little confused on what the feature matrix means. From my understanding, an example list x = [1, 2, 3,4] and an example d = 3, the matrix would have a feature matrix of [[ 1 1 1 1] where the row is the value of x and the column is the degree of d. So [[1^3 1^2 1^1, 1^0] and so on. Is this correct, or am I completely misunderstanding it? [ 8 4 2 1]               [2^3, 2^2, 2^1, 2^0] [27 9 3 1]               [3^3 3^2 ............]] [64 16 4 1]] Answer: Yeah you've got it. So if `x = [1, 2, 3]` and `d = 2` the output would be```[[1, 1, 1], [4, 2, 1], [9, 3, 1]]``` ", meta={'folders': ['hw7'], 'title': 'HW 7 feature matrix question', 'timestamp': '2022-10-21T04:00:10Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw7', 'student'], 'likes': 1, 'views': 130}),
