	Document(content="Question: On the write up it asks for the 'engagement_1' and 'engagement_2' sample information, however the files I received are 'engagement_0' and 'engagement_1'. I'm assuming this was just a mistake, but is it acceptable to still use the engagement 0 and 1 values or should I adjust it to read engagement 1 and 2? Answer: Probably a typo. Go with engagement 0 and 1", meta={'folders': ['hw5'], 'title': 'Homework 5, problem 1, question 5 write-up', 'timestamp': '2022-10-08T00:08:07Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw5', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 126}),
	Document(content="Question: For this are we still doing a t-test? I didn't really understand how knowing the population standard deviation will change our results Answer: A t-test is used if the population standard deviation is unknown and the sample size is less than 30. Otherwise use a z-test. Since the population standard deviation is known for this question, a z-test can be used.", meta={'folders': ['hw5'], 'title': 'HW 5 Problem 2 Q3', 'timestamp': '2022-10-07T20:54:25Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw5', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 115}),
