	Document(content="Question: How do we know when to use a z test compared to a t test? I know them individually I just don't know when to use each test. Answer: If the number of samples is less than 30 AND you do not know the population variance/standard deviation, use the t-test. If the number of samples is greater than 30 use the z-test. If the number of samples is less then 30 BUT you know the population variance/standard deviation, use the z-test. ", meta={'folders': ['hw5'], 'title': 'HW 5', 'timestamp': '2022-09-30T18:28:31Z', 'user': 'ktnb8chh43f2xw', 'tags': ['hw5', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 132}),
