	Document(content="Note: Hi All, Homework 4 grades have been released for all sections now. Everyone should be able to view their grading feedback in their Homework 4 repository on GitHub. To view your feedback, go to your Homework 4 repository on GitHub, click the drop down menu under ‘master/main' --> click ‘Tags’ --> click ‘graded.' There will be a file called 'grading_output.txt' in your repository with the output of the grading script specifying which test cases you passed and the number of points they were worth. Note that homework is generally graded using test cases. We run your code on a number of test cases (these test cases are visible to you in the grading_output.txt file) and assign points based on the test cases your code passes. Each test case is worth a different number of points depending on its difficulty. Also, we provide you with the test_cases.py file, which specify the tests performed on your code and the expected output in the comment. If you believe an error has been made in grading, please send a regrade request to ece20875.purdue.university@gmail.com . You have one week from the day grades are posted to Brightspace to request a regrade. Remember to include the following information in your email: When submitting an email for a regrade request please do the following: 1. Have a separate email for each HW regrade request 2. Have the subject line be the following: HW# regrade request, in this case HW4 regrade request . This makes it a lot easier for us to filter the inbox and find your email. Also, reminder to include the following information in your email: Relevant identifying information. For homeworks, a link to your GitHub repository is needed. Section Number Grading item (e.g., homework 1) Purdue email (if not sent from a Purdue email) Your reasoning or explanation for a regrade, with specific details and justification pointing to the README ", meta={'folders': ['hw4'], 'title': 'Homework 4 Grades Released!', 'timestamp': '2022-09-30T00:21:30Z', 'user': 'kskmx82xa2s4ad', 'tags': ['hw4', 'instructor-note', 'pin'], 'likes': 1, 'views': 205}),
