	Document(content="Question: Could someone explain question 5 to me on the fall 2021 practice exam Answer: To calculate the probabilities you can notice that the random process can be described by a binomial distribution. See the slides for the pmf of this distribution (recall n is the number of flips, p is the probability (of a tails, in this case) in a single flip, and x is the value that the random variable takes (0, 1, or 2; the possible number of tails from two coin flips) ", meta={'folders': ['exam'], 'title': 'Fall exam Question 5', 'timestamp': '2022-09-28T14:10:22Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['exam', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 163}),
