	Document(content="Question: Should the null hypothesis and alternative hypothesis be the average amount of dispensed soda or just the amount of soda being 300mL? If average, why? Answer: $$\mu$$ generally denotes means in this course (so if the formulas use it, we're talking about averages). You can pull up the slides on statistical testing for differences in means to see more examples and formulas. ", meta={'folders': ['exam'], 'title': 'Question 6a', 'timestamp': '2022-09-26T02:59:07Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['exam', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 107}),
