	Document(content="Question: A lot of us have our PHYS 272 exam from 6:30 to 7:30 pm, so I just wanted to know when exactly the review session will be held. Answer: The review session is held during the lecture time. ", meta={'folders': ['exam'], 'title': 'When is the review session on Tuesday?', 'timestamp': '2022-09-25T21:08:08Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['exam', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 115}),
	Document(content="Question: I didn't understand how we got p = 0.05 from the 68-95-99.7% rule, I thought that we would be given a table to find p value from z score? Answer: A 2-tailed z-score of 2 means that 95% of the area (probability) lies within the interval marked by z-score. Since p-value is the area (probability) outside that interval, the p-value would be 100%-95% = 0.05. ", meta={'folders': ['exam'], 'title': 'Question 6c Spring 2022', 'timestamp': '2022-09-25T20:05:55Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['exam', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 120}),
	Document(content="Question: I'm having trouble finding where they got the .2 and .4 from. Could anyone explain that part for me. Answer: So this section is part of question 3, so you can use the distribution given in 3a. We're looking at x<0 in the summation; the probability of -2 is 1/5 or 0.2 and the probability for -1 is 2/5 or 0.4. From there it's just a plug and chug. ", meta={'folders': ['exam'], 'title': 'Exam 1 Spring 2022 Problem 3D', 'timestamp': '2022-09-25T19:39:11Z', 'user': 'ktnb8chh43f2xw', 'tags': ['exam', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 123}),
	Document(content="Question: I'm confused with hw3 p1 test case 1-5. I try to figure by hand, but I can't match the answer with the grading report. By grading report, expected output : {4: -1.6666666666666667, 3: -1.3333333333333333} But I can't find a j value smaller than -0.5. I think the output should be {0:-0.5, 1:-1/9}. This is also the smallest value I got with my code. (Though, I didn't get the correct output from both grading reports, not sure how it to be tested in the grading ) I also manually calculate other test cases by hand and got the matched result with the grading report except for test case 1-5. Is there any other detail I didn't notice? Thanks. Answer: Our grading script actually passes in `[0.5, 0.33333333, 0.16666667]` as the data instead of `[1, 2, 3]` for this test case. The `sweep_n` function is called with `sweep_n(data=[0.5, 1/3, 1/6], minimum=0, maximum=3, min_bins=1, max_bins=10)`.Odds are your call to `plt.hist` is missing the correct `range` parameter (which we do mention in the function's doc comment). Try adding `range=(minimum, maximum)` to your call to `plt.hist` and see if you get the expected result.Still, this is an edge case of an edge case so I will bring up regrading with the GTA in charge of this homework. Thank you for bringing this to our attention (and for the detailed write-up). ", meta={'folders': ['hw3'], 'title': 'HW3 problem1 test case 1-5 question', 'timestamp': '2022-09-24T01:32:04Z', 'user': 'l4anrb9mg6n3xn', 'tags': ['hw3', 'student'], 'likes': 2, 'views': 114}),
