	Document(content="Question: In slides 17-18, we are given an example where we want to find the density function for the machine. Can the step-by-step of how you go from $$f_{X}(x)$$ to $$F_{X}(x)$$ be explained? Answer: $$F_X(x) = \int_{-\infty}^{x}f_X(t)dt = P(X \le x)$$For that specific problem, you don't need to rigorously compute the integral -- it can be done by inspection. ", meta={'folders': ['other'], 'title': 'probability2 slide example', 'timestamp': '2022-09-17T20:15:29Z', 'user': 'keuahk7t7pc1oq', 'tags': ['other', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 109}),
