	Document(content="Question: I'm getting a final J-value of this: This is awfully close to the actual value, while still being incorrect to 4 decimal spaces, so I broke it up into two numbers. The complicated 'constant' based on width and count at the front: and the sum of all the squared bin probabilities: I did both out on my calculator and came to the same numbers as I'm getting here. I'd really appreciate it if someone could tell me which half is wrong, so I know where to focus. Answer: When you are calculating j, make sure you multiply the sum of the square of the probabilities with one of the terms and not both of them. The formula is as shown - Additionally, check for operator precedence and if you are using the right order of operations as well. ", meta={'folders': ['hw3'], 'title': 'J-Value wrong', 'timestamp': '2022-09-15T23:48:38Z', 'user': 'ijllrxctkvy62', 'tags': ['hw3', 'student'], 'likes': 1, 'views': 108}),
