	Document(content="Question: How do you use matplotlib.pyplot.hist and how is sweep_n set up to output a list from the matplotlib.pyplot.hist function? Answer: Try looking at the parameters that are passed into the function and the values returned here: https://matplotlib.org/stable/api/_as_gen/matplotlib.pyplot.hist.html . Note: Not all of the parameters passed in and values returned have to be filled in or used for this problem. Try looking at what each function argument stands for. ", meta={'folders': ['hw3'], 'title': 'HW3 Problem1.py matplotlib.pyplot.hist', 'timestamp': '2022-09-15T19:17:14Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw3', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 130}),
	Document(content="Question: I'm slightly confused on what the Pk's are supposed to be in the equation of J. I'm assuming that they are the probabilities calculated in norm_histogram, but if that is true, doesn't summing all of them just equal 1? If they are not this, what are they then? Thanks in advance! Answer: They are in fact the probabilities but the values are squared so their sum will not equal 1. ", meta={'folders': ['hw3'], 'title': 'J Value Question', 'timestamp': '2022-09-15T17:36:03Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw3', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 131}),
	Document(content="Question: I am not sure if this is a problem or not, but my HW3 Problem2.py 'main' script took about 2:28.00 to process, approx. 20 seconds per dataset. I'm curious if this would prove difficult to grade. My computer is rather old, but the processor load (4C/8T) is only around ~25% CPU usage system-wide (including Excel, Word, Edge, etc.) and no threads are completely maxed. Additionally, the only process I'm calling other than the stats.probplot is math.sqrt for distance calculations. Should I try and find some workaround or is this lengthy runtime just an anticipated part of the problem, or not even that lengthy on a newer system? Answer: Don't worry about it. Certainly you can make it run faster, but no need to optimize for speed in this course. ", meta={'folders': ['hw3'], 'title': 'HW3 Problem2.py \'main\' script runs rather slow', 'timestamp': '2022-09-15T15:22:36Z', 'user': 'ktnb3zmviu033k', 'tags': ['hw3', 'student'], 'likes': 3, 'views': 144}),
