	Document(content="Note: There was a android tablet and logitech mouse left behind in EE 206 during office hours on Friday (9/9). Please make sure you are not missing anything.  ", meta={'folders': ['other'], 'title': 'Tablet and Mouse Left Behind', 'timestamp': '2022-09-10T00:47:37Z', 'user': 'ke4szf6odgwee', 'tags': ['instructor-note', 'other'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 103}),
	Document(content="Question: I've almost gotten the second test case, but like many other students, I'm getting stuck with Bill and Elon. Obviously, Bill is ~20 years older than Elon, but because my code runs through the day, then month, then year, Elon is chosen instead. What is the method so that it still works but it chooses Bill instead? Answer: You will need to have some logic that as you are adding data to your date_to_all dictionary that is able to compare the data you are adding with what is already there. In other words, what logic can you put in that checks to make sure that there is currently no data in your date_to_all dictionary that uses the same key and if there is a similar key, you will need to have some logic that will choose which data to keep. ", meta={'folders': ['hw2'], 'title': 'How to compare age by year before age by day?', 'timestamp': '2022-09-09T20:14:14Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw2', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 135}),
	Document(content="Question: I want to either be able to check my code before i submit and get confirmation it will work or get feedback on why and where my code didn't work, ideally both. I checked all default test cases in hw1 were correct and i still got points off for it. Answer: There is no autograder (yet). Some homeworks come with test suites/cases. Feel free to share extra test cases on Piazza.If you think you did HW1 correctly, you can and should submit a regrade request. ", meta={'folders': ['logistics'], 'title': 'Is there feedback or an autograder or anything?', 'timestamp': '2022-09-09T18:10:13Z', 'user': 'ke63r5ljdev3gw', 'tags': ['logistics', 'student'], 'likes': 1, 'views': 129}),
