	Document(content="Question: In the homework's introduction, it says that' Increment hist[i] by 1 for each value in data that belongs to bin i . Caution When a number is repeated in the input, increment hist[i] only once. For example, if there are three instances of 4 in data that comply with bin i , just increment hist[i] by 1, not 3.' However, in the answer, there are some '2' in the list. I'm wondering what is the condition that an 2 would appear. Answer: More than one number of data can always comply to each bin of histogram, as long as they are not duplicates. For example, if the bin's range is set to [1,2) and 1.0, 1.6 are taken as inputs, then the output value of that particular bin should be 2. ", meta={'folders': ['hw2'], 'title': 'HW2 P1 Output question', 'timestamp': '2022-09-09T04:43:12Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw2', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 147}),
	Document(content="Question: I was wondering how long after submission we should expect grades to be returned for homework. In addition, where would we find these grades and comments? Will they be posted in brightspace? Answer: You will be able to find grades and grading feedback on your GitHub repository for an assignment roughly a week after the due date, although sometimes the process may take a few extra days. Grades will also be posted in Brightspace. ", meta={'folders': ['logistics'], 'title': 'When should we expect grades to be returned for HW?', 'timestamp': '2022-09-08T22:58:13Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['logistics', 'student'], 'likes': 1, 'views': 144}),
