	Document(content="Question: Do we need to consider where the input is not an integer? (e.g 21.5) Answer: I don't think we will test your code with nonintegers. Depending on your implementation it may give undefined results. ", meta={'folders': ['hw1'], 'title': 'For homework 1 problem 2, about invalid inputs', 'timestamp': '2022-08-29T21:56:06Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw1', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 156}),
	Document(content="Question: For this problem can we hard code it for January 2022 specifically or do we need to create a general formula taking in month and year? Answer: You can hardcode it for January 2022. ", meta={'folders': ['hw1'], 'title': 'Homework1 problem 2 question', 'timestamp': '2022-08-29T18:40:44Z', 'user': 'ktnb63ymkyx5xg', 'tags': ['hw1', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 148}),
	Document(content="Question: I'm having trouble accessing the files for homework 1 and modify them. I am currently using VScode to try and connect my GitHub account, but I can't figure out how to do it. Is there a specific way I should do it? Answer: [Joseph] Have you installed Git on your computer? You will need to clone the repository locally and work on it there, then push your changes back to Git. Zhuocong's answer gives you one approach to do this but you can always use the command line.[Zhuocong] We may need Github extension for Vs code. Here's the guide: https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/editor/github ", meta={'folders': ['hw1'], 'title': 'Accessing GitHub files in VScode', 'timestamp': '2022-08-29T15:50:25Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw1', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 170}),
	Document(content="Question: Are there any code standards that we need to follow. Or we just need the programs to work and that’s it? Answer: No coding standards for this course, but if you come to office hours with incomprehensible code you may be asked to go back and comment/change variable names just so the TAs can help. ", meta={'folders': ['logistics'], 'title': 'Code standards?', 'timestamp': '2022-08-28T22:33:43Z', 'user': 'k5qw6bsz41x6ik', 'tags': ['logistics', 'student'], 'likes': 1, 'views': 200}),
	Document(content="Question: Good afternoon, I was looking at the second hw and I saw that we were given a Zeller fromula approach which is great. My question is, can we use the code in that website? Would it be considered plagiarism? Answer: No you're good, we specifically gave you that website so you're fine.In general this class is ok with you using snippets from online (not the entire homework from your friend, that is cheating and we catch people doing it every year) as long as you know what the code is doing. You should leave a comment with where you referenced the code in case we have questions. ", meta={'folders': ['hw1'], 'title': 'Using the code provided for Zeller Formula', 'timestamp': '2022-08-28T22:17:32Z', 'user': 'k5b7oio0bcz3yb', 'tags': ['hw1', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 168}),
	Document(content="Question: How exactly are we supposed to use git? Do we have to download it to our computer and if so, where do we download it from? Also how do we open up the terminal after downloading it? Answer: You'll need to install Git on your own (there will be instructions online for any operating system you're using) and you'll need to open the terminal on your own (again you can find instructions for any operating system online). We can't give exact instructions because we don't know if you're on Windows, Linux, or macOS (and we also don't know what version of each OS).If you're still having trouble, office hours have started this week and TAs will be more than happy to assist your specific problems there. ", meta={'folders': ['hw1'], 'title': 'Git Terminal/Download', 'timestamp': '2022-08-28T20:01:17Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw1', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 170}),
	Document(content="Question: When printing Yes or No for if number meets the requirements, should we literally print 'Yes' or 'No' with double quotation marks or just Yes or No? Answer: Just print the words. ", meta={'folders': ['hw1'], 'title': 'HW1 Prob1 Question on printing \'Yes\' or \'No\'', 'timestamp': '2022-08-28T19:53:43Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw1', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 157}),
	Document(content="Question: Hi, guys. Where can I find the Q0 on the syllabus ? (It is neither on bright space nor Piazza.) Appreciate! Answer: There is no Quiz 0 this semester so no need to worry about this. ", meta={'folders': ['hw1'], 'title': 'Q0?', 'timestamp': '2022-08-28T17:17:21Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw1', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 171}),
	Document(content="Question: I don't know if the weekdays are supposed to start on 1 and go to 5. This would mean that the first day in the month would be a monday or what day of the week am I supposed to start on. Answer: 1 means January first, 31 means January 31st.Update: I figured you might have meant the output of Zeller's Formula? If so, please reference https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zeller%27s_congruence ", meta={'folders': ['hw1'], 'title': 'Hw1 Problem 2', 'timestamp': '2022-08-27T22:38:04Z', 'user': 'ktnb8chh43f2xw', 'tags': ['hw1', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 175}),
	Document(content="Question: I was doing hw1, and I kept getting the error 'The term '/usr/bin/python3' is not recognized as the name of a cmdlet, function, script file, or operable program. Check the spelling of the name, or if a path was included, verify that the path is correct and try again'. But then I removed '#!/usr/bin/python3' at the top and my code started to compile. What is the purpose of this? Do we need this when we submit, and does it need to also work on my laptop? Answer: Are you on Windows? The shebang line (`#!...`) tells the operating system where to look for the Python interpreter, but on windows you won't have this file. That's fine, keep the shebang line (we need it for grading) and invoke your code with `python ` (if I guessed wrong and you're not on windows, use `python3` instead of `python`). ", meta={'folders': ['hw1'], 'title': 'Question about syntax and why code works in certain ways', 'timestamp': '2022-08-27T19:08:49Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw1', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 168}),
	Document(content="Question: Where do we find the terminal to use git clone, add, commit, etc? When I open a command terminal or terminal on Visual Studio Code, the commands don't work. Answer: Make sure that the terminal being used is the Command Prompt terminal, and not Powershell. Mine defaulted to Powershell when I first opened it. You could also not have git installed. Does `git --version` show anything when you enter that command? ", meta={'folders': ['hw1'], 'title': 'Terminal Issue', 'timestamp': '2022-08-27T15:46:52Z', 'user': 'kz5ooe8hhh2nz', 'tags': ['hw1', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 174}),
	Document(content="Question: After I type the clone command in the terminal, it prompts me to type in the username and password. The username is fine but when I try to type in the password, nothing shows up in the terminal, so I can't enter my password. I'm not sure if this relates to the problem, but it asks for my login info directly in the terminal, not in a popup window like in the video. I'm using a Jupyter notebook terminal on windows. Answer: Nothing showing up when you type your password is a security feature, your password is being typed but it’s just hiding the length of it. However, GitHub has changed it’s authentication recently. If your password still doesn’t work you may need to create a personal access token to use in place of your password. See https://docs.github.com/en/authentication/keeping-your-account-and-data-secure/creating-a-personal-access-token You may also want to consider cloning using HTTPS instead of ssh (or vice versa). Do switch between these, when you copy the clone link from your repository, you can select either HTTPS or ssh. ", meta={'folders': ['hw1'], 'title': 'Problem with cloning', 'timestamp': '2022-08-27T15:41:11Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw1', 'student'], 'likes': 1, 'views': 168}),
	Document(content="Question: I am a bit confused about the program inputs. Should there be codes that accept number inputs or should we change the number (100 and 21) to something else in order to test the program and then switch them back for submission? Answer: The code should not accept number inputs. You should change number to different values to test your code and then switch it back for submission. ", meta={'folders': ['hw1'], 'title': 'Program user inputs?', 'timestamp': '2022-08-27T00:27:19Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw1', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 151}),
	Document(content="Question: Are we allowed to use datetime (.weekday()) function for problem2? I want to make sure if using it is allowed before I start problem2. Answer: The purpose of the first assignment is mainly to just familiarize you with git and introduce you to python. This assignment will be auto-graded and so long as your program outputs the correct results given the input, it will receive full points. ", meta={'folders': ['hw1'], 'title': 'hw1 problem 2 using different approach.', 'timestamp': '2022-08-26T20:11:09Z', 'user': 'ksl0vbj3yfy5hv', 'tags': ['hw1', 'student'], 'likes': 1, 'views': 155}),
	Document(content="Question: I've just started the homework and was wondering if we should consider 0 as an accepted number input, as some sources I've seen include it as the first integer in the Fibonacci sequence and others don't. Answer: 'The Fibonacci Sequence is as follows 0, 1, 1, 2, 3, 5, 8, 13.... ' taken from the github README. However, 0 is not a positive number, so it fails one of the three conditions (positive, even, and part of the Fibonacci sequence) ", meta={'folders': ['hw1'], 'title': '0 as part of Fibonacci Sequence?', 'timestamp': '2022-08-26T19:47:44Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw1', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 168}),
	Document(content="Question: The geeks for geeks link provided with problem 1 solves the fib sequence with : # python program to check if x is a perfect square import math are we permitted to import this program in our own solutions?  Answer: In this class you can import any standard libraries whenever you want unless we explicitly say otherwise. ", meta={'folders': ['hw1'], 'title': 'import math', 'timestamp': '2022-08-26T17:48:36Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw1', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 184}),
	Document(content="Question: When will the first homework be available to start? Answer: Hi! The Homework 1 announcement will be made today at noon. ", meta={'folders': ['hw1'], 'title': 'Hw1', 'timestamp': '2022-08-26T13:51:18Z', 'user': 'ksjpssscg15ix', 'tags': ['hw1', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 194}),
	Document(content="Note: Hi students! This is just a reminder to fill out the survey linked in the syllabus that collects your Github username, section, and Purdue email: https://forms.gle/kU5c2FNZGcsyz2s79 We will be using this survey to add you to the Github Classroom for the course and identify your assignments for grading. The Github Classroom is also how you will get access to and submit homework assignments so filling out the survey is very important . I will be pulling the results of the survey sometime after 3 pm Friday afternoon so if you have not completed the survey by then you will need to reach out to a TA to get you added to the course. Thanks! ", meta={'folders': ['logistics'], 'title': 'Reminder to fill out Github survey', 'timestamp': '2022-08-24T19:25:19Z', 'user': 'ktit8n4gsw8346', 'tags': ['instructor-note', 'logistics'], 'likes': 1, 'views': 207}),
	Document(content="Question: I am not currently enrolled in an ECE 20875 Gradescope course. Should I be at this point? Or is there a code to join the Gradescope course? Answer: Gradescope will be used later in the semester for the exams. All homework submissions will be handled through github classroom. We will be pulling student github usernames from the survey in the syllabus on either Thursday or Friday to add them to the course's github classroom. ", meta={'folders': ['logistics'], 'title': 'Gradescope', 'timestamp': '2022-08-24T01:04:39Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['logistics', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 228}),
	Document(content="Question: When creating a GitHub account, does the email we create the account with have to be a Purdue email? Or can it be a personal email? Answer: It can be created with a personal email. The information we need to add you to the course GitHub classroom is your GitHub username, we then use your Purdue email to identify you for grading. ", meta={'folders': ['logistics'], 'title': 'GitHub Account', 'timestamp': '2022-08-23T23:30:45Z', 'user': 'ksp325k4vk59h', 'tags': ['logistics', 'student'], 'likes': 1, 'views': 222}),
	Document(content="Question: In lecture, Professor Qiu (Section 2) said that we would be able to see the lecture slides on Brightspace directly after the lecture. So far, I don't see anything there (unless I'm looking at the wrong place). I was wondering when I would be able to see the slides. Answer: Which section of the course are you in? ", meta={'folders': ['other', 'logistics'], 'title': 'See Lecture Slides?', 'timestamp': '2022-08-23T21:16:08Z', 'user': 'ktnb6wtmz3l2vk', 'tags': ['other', 'student'], 'likes': 1, 'views': 191}),
	Document(content="Question: As the title states, I am asking if there is a recommended Text editor or IDE for this course. There are many to choose from and wanted to know if the professor or TA's (or other students) had any that they would suggest. Thanks! Answer: Personally, I use VS Code because it works well with a bunch of languages and has a myriad of extensions. Pycharm is a nice choice if you want an IDE that just focuses on Python.Don't worry too much about your choice, many students have been successful in the class without ever leaving Vim. ", meta={'folders': ['logistics'], 'title': 'Recommended Text Editor/IDE', 'timestamp': '2022-08-23T18:29:34Z', 'user': 'k7ouja75j417oc', 'tags': ['logistics', 'student'], 'likes': 1, 'views': 224}),
	Document(content="Question: Are all the homeworks going to be due on Monday or will they be due sometime in that week. The syllabus does not clarify this. Answer: Homeworks would be due on the Friday of that particular week at 11:59pm. The first homework is due on the 2nd of September at 11:59pm ", meta={'folders': ['logistics'], 'title': 'When are hw due?', 'timestamp': '2022-08-22T21:50:29Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['logistics', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 242}),
	Document(content="Note: Piazza is a Q&A platform designed to get you great answers from classmates and instructors fast. We've put together this list of tips you might find handy as you get started: Ask questions! The best way to get answers is to ask questions! Ask questions on Piazza rather than emailing your teaching staff so everyone can benefit from the response (and so you can get answers from classmates who are up as late as you are). Edit questions and answers wiki-style. Think of Piazza as a Q&A wiki for your class. Every question has just a single students' answer that students can edit collectively (and a single instructors’ answer for instructors). Add a followup to comment or ask further questions. To comment on or ask further questions about a post, start a followup discussion . Mark it resolved when the issue has been addressed, and add any relevant information back into the Q&A above. Go anonymous. Shy? No problem. You can always opt to post or edit anonymously. Tag your posts. It's far more convenient to find all posts about your Homework 3 or Midterm 1 when the posts are tagged. Type a “#” before a key word to tag. Click a blue tag in a post or the question feed to filter for all posts that share that tag. Format code and equations. Adding a code snippet? Click the pre or tt button in the question editor to add pre-formatted or inline teletype text. Mathematical equation? Click the Fx button to access the LaTeX editor to build a nicely formatted equation. View and download class details and resources. Click the Course Page button in your top bar to access the class syllabus, staff contact information, office hours details, and course resources—all in one place!Contact the Piazza Team anytime with questions or comments at team@piazza.com . We love feedback!", meta={'folders': [], 'title': 'Welcome to Piazza!', 'timestamp': '2022-08-19T14:06:06Z', 'user': 'gd6v7134AUa', 'tags': ['student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 167})
